lks at the hotel were great. One staffer would push the elevator button when she saw me coming in and often ask how my day had gone. the concierge found a great seat for me at Hair when I grew weary of standing in the half price line for tickets one day. Several times I asked them to make change for me which they did readily at the front desk and they were always cheerful. One day I needed utensils for take-out I had picked up and a staff person went in the back and came back with plastic forks, spoons, and knives. I was just so pleased by the caring attitude of the people at the hotel. They delivered a fridge to my room so i was able to buy take-out and food from markets and eat in when I chose.I did have a problem with other guests who allowed their children to spend great lengths of time on the lobby computers. These kids would be playing games when I needed to print my boarding passes and I think a sign that says please limit your usage of computers in consideration of other guests or something would help. There were two machines and one night a teenager was instant messaging her friends for more than an hour and I finally asked her if I could please have the computer just to check the schedule of one event and then i would return it to her. She grudgingly agreed. On the night I needed to print the pass i did not think the parents of the kids would ever allow me a turn, but they finally did leave with their kids in tow.I would definitely stay here again. The location is great. it is on a quiet street and there is little noise on the backside of the hotel. The rooms have nice flat panel TVs with premium channels, comfortable beds, and are very clean. There is a small wardrobe in the room--no closets and the dresser area has drawers to store clothes--there is free internet in the rooms and good lighting. The only thing I missed was the lack of room service but there was one menu of a nearby place that delivers and a list of places nearby that offered delivery so in a pinch that would do.Do try the ethnic places in hell's kitchen. I plan to write reviews of many of them when I get time as I had some great dining experiences at very low cost. The entire trip was just under a thousand dollars and it included multiple plays, transportation, great food and lodging for five days so I met my goal of biting off the Big Apple without breaking the bank!	
