Apr 30 2009 	Great location great value.	We just got back from a 4 night stay at the Fairfield and overall had a great experience. The greatest thing I would have to say about it is the location. Having never been to New York before, I really enjoyed Times Square. We were able to send the kids off during the day and let them roam the shops like the Toys r Us, M&amp;M's Store, Quicksilver etc. The area is very safe and there is a lot to do within a few blocks.We booked through NewYorkGuest.com and got a good deal on Broadway tickets bundled into our stay. We saw 9 to 5, which also is excellent, and the hotel was close enough that we could just walk to the show. Lots of good dining in this area as well, with a lot more of the local establishments on 9th ave. Overall we found the hotel to be very clean and comfortable. The staff was very accommodating, and the free breakfast was great as well. Saving that one meal really makes the difference in New York, because most food places are fairly expensive. You really get a lot for your money here, and we will probably stay here again when we come back to NY.	
Apr 19 2009 	Very good hotel; not greatest street	The only thing wrong with this hotel was the street it is on. Was dirty but a little dodgy too (with adult shops, liquor shops) on the 8th Avenue end. The construction going on down the street was also a put off.My only other gripe would be the breakfast which was included in the room rate - not a hot breakfast. Bagels, muffins, coffee and served on paper plates and plastic cutlery - not classy by any means.But it served its purpose for us - nice sized rooms in very good location - minutes walk away from Times Square, Madison Square Garden, Empire State Building, Macys, Broadway shows, Pier 83 (for Circle Line Cruise) - 5th Ave, Central Park a $5 cab away. Cab rank right around corner in front of Port Authority - very handy.Also had mini-gym downstairs (2 treadmills, 1 bike, 2 cross trainers, dumb bells, swiss balls) which is great for those wanting to burn all those fast food, 24 diner calories!The rate was also very competitive with others we had checked.	
