Apr 9 2009 	Not a place I'll come back to.	The hotel is new, the rooms are ok for me, smaller than the rooms at the Residence Inn on 6th Ave. The closet was too much but it does have a big HDTV in the room. Hotel is down a side street, which is a dirty street and next door to the New York State Parole board, and a row of adult video stores. If you are willing to see past that, it is near to Time Square and 9th Ave, where the reasonable restaurants are, and the subway. The staff was the worse of all the Marriott properties I have stayed at, pretty indifferent, clinical and not very helpful. There was no self-service/coin operated launderette (the in-room information guide mentioned that there was). Not sure if it's a NY practice, but they provides only dry-cleaning service, no regular laundry service. And what pisses me off was that you had to take your laundry to the Front Desk, they will not pick it up from your room !Breakfast was nothing to shout about and the breakfast area was often full with no place to sit if you head down slightly later.Not a place I'll come back to.	
Mar 24 2009 	Great Stay at The Fairfield Inn	My 18 year old daughter and I loved the Fairfield Inn! We were in New York City for shopping, museums and shows. The hotel was very comfortable, although the rooms were on the small side. The hotel had only been open for two weeks so everything was very clean and the beds were very comfortable. The staff was very helpful and friendly. The breakfast was very good with a large variety of items and coffee was available all day. The location was very close to the subway stop right across the street on the corner of 40th and 8th avenue. I would love to stay there on my next trip.	
Mar 23 2009 	Not quite ready for Prime Time	This property is very new. The rooms are very small and the hotel is situated on an unappealing, noisy, dirty street alongside of the New York Port Authority and next door to the New York State Parole board. We did not feel threatened at any time but we did not want to be on that part of 40th St. for long. The hotel is clean, attractively appointed, comfortable but very much crammed into a small space which is expected in New York City. The staff was pleasant and helpful, in keeping with expectations of a Marriott property. The room was not made up by 4:30 in the afternoon when we were ready to rest for awhile after a busy day. Half a block away is 9th street that has many excellent and not very expensive (by NYC standards) restaurants.	
